			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2010</a> paper:</span><br><i>Extending DMM Behavior Specifications for Visual Execution and Debugging</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/NilsBandener.html">Nils Bandener</a>, <a href="../profile/ChristianSoltenborn.html">Christian Soltenborn</a>, <a href="../profile/GregorEngels.html">Gregor Engels</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-19440-5_24">10.1007/978-3-642-19440-5_24</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4f.html"><span class="tagM">T4F: Visualisation</span></a><ul><li> The work emphasizes visual execution and debugging, i.e., visualization of runtime behavior and debugging feedback.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1c.html"><span class="tagL">T1C: Behavioural Semantics</span></a><ul><li> It builds on behavioral/executable specifications of DMM models to enable execution and debugging.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> The contribution includes tool support to execute and debug models in a visual manner.
</li></ul></li></ul>
